{
  "doc_id": "43472",
  "text": "To the best of our knowledge, the only article where ρ is not constant is by Benth and Karlsen [CITATION_1] who study a Markovian setting with ρ = ρ(Z s ) depending on the present level of the nontraded asset Z. They show that the minimal entropy martingale measure can be expressed in terms of the solution of a semilinear PDE for which they prove existence and uniqueness of a classical solution. However, they have no claim B and they also do not derive any general explicit formulas.",
