      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "To the best of our knowledge, the only article where ρ is not constant is by Benth and Karlsen [CITATION_1] who study a Markovian setting with ρ = ρ(Z s ) depending on the present level of the nontraded asset Z. They show that the minimal entropy martingale measure can be expressed in terms of the solution of a semilinear PDE for which they prove existence and uniqueness of a classical solution.",
